### Location

Situated directly on MA Route 110, a high traffic corridor between Haverhill and Salisbury.

### Sale

Faulkner & Associates is pleased to offer for sale this mixed-use property situated directly on busy Route 110 in Amesbury, MA. The commercially zoned property consists of a 1932 Morton Steel building on a .39 acre corner lot. The building has no structurally supporting walls on the interior, so existing walls can be removed entirely or reconfigured to fit any need. The building features 3 Phase power, drive in capability (current owner replaced an overhead with a double casement door), and abundant parking.

Amesbury is presently experiencing commercial growth, and the newly constructed The Heights Amesbury apartment complex is approximately an eighth of a mile away on Route 110.  According to the MA DOT, traffic count is 6,918 vehicles per day in 2017.

Please do not inquire within, there is an operating business that is not for sale. Contact Faulkner & Associates for a private tour at your convenience.

### Power

3 Phase Power

property_description:
### Location

This property abuts to conservation land for more enjoyable walks in the woods as well as a short 1/2 mile walk up the road for a dip, or fishing in Lucas Pond.

### Sale

You won't believe this one till you see it. Completely renovated down to the studs by current owners. This light-filled home is meticulously, lovingly maintained. Kitchen with gorgeous natural wood and natural lighting. Opens onto a deck in the rear for privacy and those morning coffee moments. Take in the beautiful land that surrounds you. Dining room and living room are open to the kitchen, but the dining can be secluded for intimate moments by quaint pocket doors. Three bedrooms upstairs with beautiful full bath provide ample size rooms for all. Unfinished attic space is a clear bonus. But wait....the entry way between the attached 2 car garage is a perfect "mudroom" for this weather. Off the rear is another room with entrance to rear deck, but has been used as puppy incubator room. Did I say that this property is actively used as a home business? You would never know from the pristine housekeeping. A kennel building behind the home houses 14 kennels, office space and a "puppy" room. This building has own electric subpanel. There are runs outside of this building and a fenced in play yard. Don't think that is enough? Home is wired for generator for those unforeseen moments. AND there is a barn further down in a fenced in pasture. It is capable of providing shelter to 2 horses.
